LORE deltari
FLAGS DELTARI
- River delta folk of the Kowloon region; amphibious-adapted; heirs of the
  Reed Ledger Wardens' practical tradition
- Translucent eyelid membrane (shimmer when blinking rapidly) protects eyes
  underwater; smooth, water-repellent skin; hair stays mostly dry after
  full submersion
- Acute hearing for low-frequency sounds: deep water rumble, subsonic creature
  communication, "death-hum" of underwater structural failure; press ear to
  cistern walls as casual habit
- "Reading the flow": perceptual intelligence for water, current, weather, and
  complex interconnected systems; other races call it uncanny intuition
- Kowloon connection: Deltari communities in northern quarter lanes often work
  as archivists and cartographers; Littoral Branch writing system research
  connects them to Jade Magistracy scholarship
- Generations of adapting to environments that killed careless people: observe
  first, record second, act based on both
~
